The paper deals with algorithms for decision problems on finite structures, which are typically studied in the context of databases (cs.DB) and logic (cs.LO). The use of treewidth and MSO logic also suggests connections to graph algorithms (cs.DS, cs.CC). Finally, the mention of experimental results with a prototype implementation suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
